nsion pot.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>With ‘relief at source’, you’ll only see your contributions on your payslip.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If you pay higher or additional rate Income Tax, you may be able to <a href=\"/income-tax-reliefs/pension-contributions-tax-relief\" title=\"Pension contributions: tax relief\">claim money back</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Tracing lost pensions</h2>\n\n<p>If you lose track of pensions that you&rsquo;ve paid into over the years, the <a href=\"/find-lost-pension\" title=\"Find a lost pension\">Pension Tracing Service</a> could help you find them.</p>\n\n<h2>Nominate someone to get your pension if you die</h2>\n\n<p>You may be able to nominate (choose) someone to get your pension if you die before reaching the scheme&rsquo;s pension age. You can do this when you first join the pension or by writing to your provider.  </p>\n\n<p>Ask your pension provider if this is possible and how much the person would get. </p>\n\n<p>You can change your nomination at any time. It&rsquo;s important to keep this information and the person&rsquo;s contact details up to date. </p>\n\n<p>Sometimes the pension provider can pay the money to someone else (eg if the person you nominated can&rsquo;t be found or has died).</p>\n\n<h2>How your pension is paid</h2>\n\n<p>When you want to start getting your pension, you&rsquo;ll need to <a href=\"/personal-pensions-your-rights/how-your-pension-is-paid\" title=\"how a pension is paid\">decide how you want it to be paid</a>.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/workplace-pensions/changing-jobs-and-taking-leave","slug":"changing-jobs-and-taking-leave","order":6,"title":"Changing jobs and taking leave","body":"<h2>If you change jobs</h2>\n\n<p>Your workplace pension still belongs to you. If you don&rsquo;t carry on paying into the scheme, the money will still be invested and you&rsquo;ll get a pension when you reach the scheme&rsquo;s pension age.</p>\n\n<p>You can join another workplace scheme if you 